"'''Sandstorm'''" is a twelve-page comic appearing in ''[[Star Wars Tales 15]]'' and collected in ''[[Star Wars Tales Volume 4]]''.

==Plot summary==
[[File:Krayt_Sandstorm.jpg|thumb|left|180px|A [[Krayt dragon/Legends|Krayt dragon]] attacks [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke]] and [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Ani]].]]

On [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]], [[Owen Lars/Legends|Owen]] and [[Beru Whitesun Lars/Legends|Beru Lars]] discuss their 10 year old nephew [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]]. Owen has refused to tell Luke more about his father, and in anger Luke runs away. Unfortunately, a sandstorm moves in at the same time, and soon Luke is lost in the desert. He has a vision of a tall dark figure, and shortly afterwards meets a young boy named [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Annie]]. The two boys realize they have much in common&mdash;neither knows much about their father, they are both great pilots, they both want to leave Tatooine some day, and they can [[The Force/Legends|sense]] things before they happen. They soon discover a [[Tusken Raider/Legends|Tusken Raider]] buried in the sand, and taking his [[Gaderffii/Legends|gaffi stick]] they seek shelter in a nearby cave. A pack of [[Womp rat/Legends|womp rats]] drives them back out into the storm, where they stumble upon a [[R5-D4/Legends|red and white]] [[Astromech droid/Legends|astromech droid]]. Annie rigs up the astromech's motivator to explode, sending up a flare. This attracts the attention of a [[Krayt dragon/Legends|krayt dragon]], who attacks the two boys. Luke loses sight of Annie, and on instinct throws the gaffi stick into the throat of the dragon, killing it. Luke falls unconscious. When Owen and a rescue party find him later, there is no sign of the krayt dragon or Annie. Luke is certain it was more than just a dream, and Owen knows there is something special about his nephew.

